ABUJA – The All Progressives Congress (APC) has announced the postponement of meetings of its National Caucus and National Executive Committee (NEC) earlier scheduled to hold Monday and Tuesday, July 10th and 11th respectively, in Abuja. The meetings will now hold on the 18th and 19th respectfully, according to a terse statement signed Sunday night by Senator Iyiola Omisore, the party’s National Secretary. The postponement, he said, was necessitated by “the regional and sub-regional schedules and engagements of President Bola Ahmed Tinubu, GCFR, as the new Chairman of the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS). 